    <paragraph id="3.13.10.4.13" type="REQUIREMENT" scope="OBU" >In case of target EOA/SvL without any supervised release speed, the Table 7 and Table 9 shall be applied, by substituting V_release with the value 0.</paragraph>
    <paragraph id="3.13.10.4.14" type="NOTE" scope="OBU" >Note: as long as the same MRSP or LOA target is displayed, the on-board will revoke the Indication status only when the estimated speed does no longer exceed the target speed. On the other hand, as long as the same EOA/SvL target is displayed, the Indication status, once it is triggered, is never revoked. However, for all types of target and only in case of MRDT change, the on-board will revoke the Indication status if the Indication supervision limit (speed and location) is not exceeded (see Table 8 and Table 9).</paragraph>
    <paragraph id="3.13.10.4.15" type="REQUIREMENT" scope="OBU" >The on-board equipment shall execute the transitions between the different supervision statuses as described in Table 10 (see section 4.6.1 for details about the symbols). This table takes into account the order of precedence between the supervision statuses and the possible changes of the displayed target (MRDT), e.g. when the list of supervised targets is updated.</paragraph>
