    <paragraph id="3.A3.4" type="TITLE" scope="OBU">Handling of Stored Information in specific Situations</paragraph>
    <paragraph id="3.A3.4.1" type="TITLE" scope="OBU">Introduction</paragraph>
    <paragraph id="3.A3.4.1.1" type="REQUIREMENT" optional="TRUE" scope="OBU">All data that can be stored onboard may be influenced in special situations.</paragraph>
    <paragraph id="3.A3.4.1.2" type="DEFINITION" scope="OBU">The situations acting on the "status" of stored information are:
a) the execution of a conditional emergency stop (3.7.3.3, 3.10.2.1.2);
b) the reception of a shortened MA (3.7.3.3);
c) the stored MA is shortened due to a section time-out (3.7.3.3, 3.8.4.2.2);
d) the SvL is shifted (to the DP if any or to the EOA) due to an overlap time-out (3.8.4.4.2) ;
e) the stored MA is shortened due to an end section time-out (3.7.3.3, 3.8.4.1.2);
f) a cooperative MA revocation is granted by the onboard (3.8.6.2);
g) inconsistency in a balise group marked as unlinked (3.16.2.5.2);
h) a linking reaction led to a service brake and the train is at standstill (3.16.2.6.2) ;
i) the reaction due to the supervision of the safe radio connection led to a service brake and the train is at standstill (3.16.3.4.5 b) ;
j) the train category, axle load, loading gauge or power supply is changed (3.18.3.7) ;
k) driver closes the desk during SoM ;
l) RAMS related supervision functions led to a service brake and train is at standstill (3.16.2.7)
m) inconsistency in a balise group marked as linked and no linking is used onboard (3.16.2.4.4.2)</paragraph>
    <paragraph id="3.A3.4.1.3" type="DEFINITION" scope="OBU">Depending on the situation, the action can be:
a) data is deleted,
b) data is reset (set to initial states)
c) data status is unchanged,
d) data is to be revalidated</paragraph>
    <paragraph id="3.A3.4.1.3.1" type="NOTE" scope="OBU">D = Deleted U = Unchanged R = Reset TBR = To Be Revalidated</paragraph>
