    <paragraph id="4.5.1.1" type="DEFINITION" scope="OBU">The following table specifies in which modes the on-board functions are active or not. The functions are described in the "Related SRS paragraph " (second column of the table).</paragraph>
    <paragraph id="4.5.1.2" type="DEFINITION" scope="OBU">Note: Modes are not the only thing that can influence an onboard function. This is why this Table is not enough in itself to understand all the ERTMS/ETCS onboard behaviour. It must be understood as a complement to all other SRS chapters (especially paragraph 4.7, 4.8, 4.9 and 4.10).</paragraph>
    <paragraph id="4.5.1.3" type="NOTE" scope="OBU" >Note: for DMI depending on modes, refer to paragraph 4.7.</paragraph>
